@{
    ViewData["Title"] = " Speaker Recognition API";
}
<h1 class="display-4">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>


    Want to try out using your own personal voice from your own personal mouth to create a voiceprint using AI?!
    Sure you do. And here's where you can try that out.

<h2> No API key yet?</h2>

    Go and get your cognitive services <strong>API key</strong> at <a href="https://portal.azure.com">portal.azure.com</a> and your cognitive services <strong>endpoint</strong>.

<h2>Already got an API key and Endpoint?</h2>

<ol>
    <li>
        Paste them in here and click "go":<br />
        <form method="GET" action="@Url.Action("SpeakerRecognitionDemo", "Home")">
            <input type="text" name="endpoint" style="width:300px" placeholder="endpoint">https://nextgenvoiceloginapi.cognitiveservices.azure.com/spid/v1.0<br />
            <input type="text" name="key" style="width:300px" placeholder="key"><br />
            <input type="submit" value="go">
        </form>
    </li>
    <li>Click "Enrol" and talk for 15 seconds</li>
    <li>Wait to be asked your name</li>
    <li>Repeat for another person</li>
    <li>When you've done a few people, click "Identify" and only one person talk</li>
    <li>HOPEFULLY the correct person will be identified!</li>
</ol>

